memories.title: Harvard's Itatti Library for Renaissance Studies
memories.description: Discovered the Villa I Tatti library, Harvard University's center for Italian Renaissance studies. Contains rare manuscripts and resources for scholars studying Renaissance art, history, and culture. The library houses over 175,000 volumes, a photo archive with 250,000 photographs, and a collection of historic prints.

memories.title: Essential Elitist Anime
memories.description: A interest stack made by GentleDragonite full of anime that are deep, philisophical, surreal, atmospheric, thought provoking, unconventional and most of all confusing.

memories.title: MIT's Open Courseware on Quantum Computing
memories.description: Found MIT's comprehensive open courseware on quantum computing fundamentals, including lecture videos, notes, and problem sets. The course covers quantum mechanics principles relevant to computation, quantum gates and circuits, quantum algorithms (including Shor's and Grover's algorithms), quantum error correction, and physical implementations of quantum computers.

memories.title: The Internet Archive's Book Collection
memories.description: Explored the Internet Archive's vast collection of digitized books, including rare and out-of-print volumes on computer science history. The Internet Archive has digitized millions of books, many of which are no longer in print or commercially available.

memories.title: Elitist Anime
memories.description: "Elitist" has been a very generic and broad term to generalise many types of not-so-mainstream or "deep" anime, so this list is very diverse and its criteria are not always clear cut and objective. Nonetheless I try to provide a proper explanation for why each entry is included. Generally speaking these are shows that fit one OR more of these adjectives: Experimental, Avant-Garde, Psychological, Philosophical, Obscure, Classic, Critically Acclaimed, Artsy, Old, etc... Some shows here are not necessarily obscure or underground at all, but they are still here because they have been stereotyped as "elitist" by the community over time, due to their experimental or artsy nature. Similarly, some shows here are not necessarily artsy or experimental in nature, but their old/underwatched/obscure nature gives them a reason to be here. Not all aspects have to be checked to be included. Only one per franchise. I have personally watched the great majority of the anime in this list, but there are a couple which I haven't. Still added them because of how strongly they are stereotyped as "elitist" or have fitting characteristics to be classified as such. I know my list still lacks many essential classics, I will continue to add and expand into this list as I watch those personally. For more recommendations, go to my other Interest Stacks, "Elitist Anime 2", "Elitist Anime 3" and "Elitist Anime 4", whose links are: - https://myanimelist.net/stacks/4256 - https://myanimelist.net/stacks/4756 - https://myanimelist.net/stacks/10188 - https://myanimelist.net/stacks/15961
